July 20, 1923
My Dear little girl; 
If you could know how many times I think of you; it might be some compen-sation for my tardy letter writing has been so hard this summer. For weeks I have not been well, Have been to "blue hole" but once this summer, but Mona has been going, little alice to and they can hardly get her out. She tells Daddy "No sir I swim" and back she wades. I was so glad for your letter weeks ago and I hope you are having a pleasant vacation. So glad to know you have bot the home and how pretty it must be all <unclear/>. 
I hope you will get into Soo City to teach. They have been having a great time here for teachers this summer the school is much better unclear the new <unclear/> and wages are better but teacher have so much to do I did not want you to have so much work, but oh! I did want you here. Mary House of Wayne was elected to the Primary at $10. I board here for $20, she is a dear little girl but I did so wish it were you to be here.  

