y yard has been so beautiful this summer and I have a lovely garden. 
Mother has gone to Lincoln I hardly expect her back again. With there she can go out in their car. Here she could not get around. 
The weather has been so hot here. John is gone again and I am doing the milking, we are making cheese too, we make a 2lb cheese every other day. And we have 5 of them now. I don't need to can peaches this year I have so many left I think of you every time I open a can. How you did help. And I wish you were her this Summer. Peaches are not so plentiful this year melons too are scarce, they had to give up for the tobacco craze. Every one is raining tobacco this year. Lots of plums and apples I have such lots of ripe tomatoes. Must can this week get Mrs. Garner always asks for you and so do the Balls. I have not been out there this summer. Think I shall go before school begins. Remember me to your father and mother all the boys and your own dear self I am so glad for the sweet photo of yourself lovingly Alice Neihardt
